+--------------------------------------------------------------------+
| Classified US Intel Budget Revealed Via Powerpoint                 |
|   from the woops-they-did-it-again dept.                           |
|   posted by CmdrTaco on Monday June 11, @10:05 (United States)     |
|   http://it.slashdot.org/article.pl?sid=07/06/11/132205            |
+--------------------------------------------------------------------+

[0]Atario writes "In a holdover from the Cold War when the number really
did matter to national security, the size of the US national intelligence
budget remains one of the government's most closely guarded secrets. The
Office of the Director of National Intelligence, the highest intelligence
agency in the country that oversees all federal intelligence agencies,
appears to have [1]inadvertently released the keys to that number in an
unclassified PowerPoint presentation now posted on the website of the
Defense Intelligence Agency (DIA). By reverse engineering the numbers in
an underlying data element embedded in the presentation, it seems that
the total budget of the 16 US intelligence agencies in fiscal year 2005
was $60 billion, almost 25% higher than previously believed."

Discuss this story at:
    http://it.slashdot.org/comments.pl?sid=07/06/11/132205

Links:
    0. http://www.bannination.com/
    1. http://www.thespywhobilledme.com/the_spy_who_billed_me/2007/06/exclusive_offic.html


